# Makefile Conventions

## Target Structure
- `install` - Copy all scripts and icons to KiCAD plugins directory
- `clean` - Remove only project-specific files (selective cleanup)
- `clean-all` - Remove all files from target directory (complete cleanup)

## Path Conventions
- Target directory: `$(HOME)/Documents/KiCAD/9.0/scripting/plugins/`
- Source files: `scritps/*.py scritps/*.png`
- Use `$(HOME)` for portable home directory reference

## User Feedback
- All messages must be in English
- Use `@echo` for user-facing messages
- Show progress and completion status
- Display file modification times after installation

## File Operations
- Use `cp` for installation (preserves file attributes)
- Use `rm -f` for selective cleanup (ignores missing files)
- Use `rm -rf` for complete cleanup (recursive force)
- Use `find` with proper escaping for file operations

## Error Handling
- Use `-f` flag with `rm` to avoid errors on missing files
- Use `@` prefix to suppress command echo in output
- Provide clear status messages for each operation